This article is a fact sheet highlighting the Obama Administration's efforts to promote equality and justice for the LGBT community. It discusses various initiatives and achievements, including the passage of the Matthew Shepard and James Byrd, Jr. Hate Crimes Prevention Act, the repeal of the Don't Ask Don't Tell policy, the recognition of same-sex marriages, the protection of LGBT individuals against discrimination, and the advancement of LGBT rights globally. The article also mentions the administration's focus on preventing bullying and hate crimes, supporting LGBT health, ensuring equality in housing and crime prevention, and recognizing LGBT history and contributions.